To build for the first time you must run
    cmake --preset=default
first.

To cross compile for aarch64 you must install an arm c and c++ compiler
    sudo apt install gcc-aarch64-linux-gnu
    sudo apt install g++-aarch64-linux-gnu

To then build the executable run
    cmake --build build
Telling the compiler to build the project in the build dir

Ninja is required for building the base project
    sudo apt install ninja-build

These are the packages needed to build SDL3
    sudo apt install autoconf autoconf-archive automake libtool
    sudo apt-get install libxtst-dev
    sudo apt install python3.12-venv


Might need
    sudo apt install xsltproc



